# Next.js & React

## Server vs client

- **Server components** by default in `app/`. Add `'use client'` only when using hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers.
- Keep `page.tsx` thin; pass Clerk user data from server pages into client shells (e.g. `DashboardClient`).

## Routing

- Auth: `app/sign-in/[[...sign-in]]/`, `app/sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/`
- Protected UI: `app/dashboard/` — auth enforced in `app/dashboard/page.tsx` + `middleware.ts`
- Home splash: `app/components/HomeEntry.tsx` via `app/page.tsx`

## API routes

- `app/api/generate/route.ts` — authenticated SSE pipeline; do not merge AI stages into one mega-prompt (JSON truncation).

## Components

- One default export per file in `app/components/`.
- Onboarding: `OnboardingGuide` + `GuideEngineer` + `GuideSpeechBubble`; persistence in `lib/onboarding.ts`.

## Images

Use `next/image` for static assets under `public/` (e.g. `/alex-engineer.png`).
